<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features: CounterParty Maintenance" role="TOPIC">
  <title>CounterParty Maintenance</title>
  
   <section>
    <title>Overview</title>

    <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a bank, you can accept or reject new counterparty 
	created by the customer. </para>
</section>
  
  <section role="ITEM">
  <title>Associate CounterParty</title>
  
  	<para>You can view and modify the counterparties that are associated to a 
  	customer or in pending.</para>
  	<para>To navigate to the Associate CounterParty function, from the tool bar, 
  	select System Features  > CounterParty Maintenance. Then select Associate 
  	CounterParty from the left side navigation menu.</para>
  	<para>To use this function, click the Search Options link to display the fields 
  	that can be used to filter the list. These are <emphasis role="bold">CounterParty Abbv Name,
  	 Company Abbv Name and Association Status </emphasis>fields. To display all records, 
  	 enter an asterisk in any of the criteria fields.</para>
  	<para>The columns returned in the list of Associated counterparty are the following:</para>
     
         		    	
  	    <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="6.0*" />

          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry nameend="c2" namest="c1" valign="top"><para
              role="TEXT">Field</para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Description</para></entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry valign="middle"><para role="TEXT"> <guiicon
              moreinfo="none">CounterParty Abbv Name</guiicon> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top">Abbreviated name of the counterparty.</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="middle"><para role="TEXT"> <guiicon
              moreinfo="none">Company Abbv Name</guiicon> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Abbreviated name of the company link 
              to the counterparty</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="middle"><para role="TEXT"> <guiicon
              moreinfo="none">Customer Associated to Counterparty</guiicon> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Abbreviated name of the customer 
              link to this counterparty.</para></entry>
            </row>

    <row>
              <entry valign="middle"><para role="TEXT"> <guiicon
              moreinfo="none">Association status</guiicon> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">The status of the association 
              (pending / associated)</para></entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry valign="middle"><para role="TEXT"> <guiicon
              moreinfo="none">Creation Date</guiicon> </para></entry>

              <entry valign="top"><para role="TEXT">Date of the request of association.</para></entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
     
      <para>Each record is shown with one or more of the following action icons to the left of the entry, 
      depending on its status:</para>
      
            <informaltable role="TEXT">
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2.0*" />

          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="8.0*" />

          <thead>
